####################################################################
# How to compile:
####################################################################
1. SDL.
	You will need to have the SDL library installed.
	The path of the SDL source file is assumed to be:
		/usr/include/SDL/
	If this is not the case then you need to update the path in:
		make-run.sh 

2. Compile.
	Run the make script:
	  ./make-run.sh
	A binary file zikibg will be created.

3. Run and play.
	Run zikibg to play.
	  ./zikibg

####################################################################
# In game instructions:
####################################################################
1. To exit the game ESC
2. The yellow chip indicates which side currently has the turn.
3. Left click on each dice to roll, there is no animation,
   the numbers will change but not always so if the numbers dont 
   change then you may have just rolled the same numbers again.
4. Once you have rolled your dice the left click on a chip that you 
   want to pick-up and then left click on the triangle you want to 
   drop it on.
5. If you have picked-up a chip but changed your mind, then right-click
   and it will be returned.
6. There is no scoring.
7. There is no AI.
8. There is no network play.
9. You are playing both sides at this stage.
